# Mobile-first responsive UI — agent reference

Every UI component in this project must work correctly at **375 px** (iPhone SE), **390 px** (iPhone 15), **768 px** (iPad), **1024 px** (laptop), and **1440 px** (desktop). Design mobile first; use Tailwind breakpoints to scale up, not down.

## 1. Breakpoint strategy

Use **Tailwind's default min-width breakpoints** in this order:

| Prefix | Min width | Context |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| _(none)_ | 0 px | Mobile default — design here first |
| `sm:` | 640 px | Large phone / small tablet |
| `md:` | 768 px | Tablet portrait |
| `lg:` | 1024 px | Laptop — sidebar becomes visible |
| `xl:` | 1280 px | Desktop |

**Rules:**
- Write the mobile style first (no prefix), then add `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` overrides.
- Never write desktop-only styles without a mobile fallback.
- Never use `max-w-` breakpoints (max-width queries); always min-width.

## 2. Layout — admin dashboard

The admin shell (`AdminLayout`) follows this pattern:

```
Mobile (<lg):
  ┌────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Topbar (56px sticky)               │
  │  [K] Bookings      [refresh] [+]   │
  ├────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Page content (scrolls)             │
  │  p-3 sm:p-4 lg:p-6                 │
  └────────────────────────────────────┘

Desktop (lg+):
  ┌──────────┬─────────────────────────┐
  │ Sidebar  │ Topbar (56px sticky)    │
  │ (fixed,  ├─────────────────────────┤
  │  220px)  │ Page content            │
  │          │  p-5 lg:p-6             │
  └──────────┴─────────────────────────┘
```

- Sidebar is `hidden lg:flex` + `position: fixed`.
- Main area uses `lg:pl-[220px]` to offset from the fixed sidebar.
- On mobile, the **topbar** is the sole navigation surface.

## 3. Touch targets

All interactive elements must meet **WCAG 2.5.5 (AAA) / iOS HIG**: minimum **44 × 44 px**.

```tsx
// ✅ Good — icon button with explicit min size
<button className="p-2.5 rounded-lg min-w-[44px] min-h-[44px] flex items-center justify-center">

// ❌ Bad — icon button too small
<button className="p-1 rounded">
```

Table row actions, filter buttons, nav items, and pagination chips must all meet this threshold. Use `py-2.5` or `min-h-[44px]` on any tappable element.

## 4. Typography scaling

| Use | Mobile | Desktop |
|-----|--------|---------|
| Page title | `text-base font-bold` | `text-[14px] font-bold` |
| Table data | `text-sm` | `text-[13px]` |
| Secondary / muted | `text-xs` | `text-[11px]` |
| Section labels | `text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider` | same |

Prefer Tailwind `text-sm` / `text-base` on mobile; use precise `text-[13px]` pixel values for desktop density.

## 5. Tables

Tables must never cause horizontal overflow on the page. Use this pattern:

```tsx
<div className="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl"> {/* scrollable wrapper */}
  <table className="w-full min-w-[600px]">   {/* ensures table doesn't collapse */}
    ...
  </table>
</div>
```

Hide non-critical columns on small screens:

| Column | Visible from |
|--------|-------------|
| Status | always |
| Guest (name + email) | always |
| Stay (dates + nights) | always |
| Pax | `md:` |
| Flags (parking/pet icons) | `sm:` |
| Amount | `lg:` |
| Created | `md:` |
| Actions | always (icon only on mobile) |

## 6. Forms and filter bars

- Search input: always full-width (`w-full`).
- Filter button strips: `overflow-x-auto` horizontal scroll on mobile — never wrap into multiple rows.
- Dropdown panels: position absolute, `max-h-[60vh] overflow-y-auto`, with a max-width of `min(90vw, 320px)` to avoid viewport overflow.
- Input height: `h-10` (40 px) minimum — touch friendly.

## 7. Spacing

| Context | Mobile | Desktop |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Page padding | `p-3 sm:p-4` | `lg:p-6` |
| Card / section gap | `space-y-3` | `sm:space-y-4` |
| Form field gap | `space-y-4` | same |
| Inline button gap | `gap-1.5` | same |

Never use `px-6` or larger without a mobile fallback like `px-4`.

## 8. Images and media

- Always set explicit `width` + `height` or use `aspect-*` classes.
- Use `object-cover` on images inside fixed containers.
- Never use `<img>` inside a flex container without `shrink-0` or `min-w-0`.

## 9. Modals and dropdowns

- Modals: full-screen on mobile (`fixed inset-0`) → centered card on `sm:` (`sm:inset-auto sm:rounded-xl`).
- Dropdowns: on mobile, dropdown panels must never overflow the viewport. Apply `max-w-[calc(100vw-24px)]` as a safety net.
- Use `z-50` for overlays, `z-40` for sticky headers.

## 10. Don'ts

- Don't hardcode pixel widths that assume desktop: `width: 800px` without `max-w-full`.
- Don't use `whitespace-nowrap` on text that should wrap at mobile sizes.
- Don't hide entire feature sections behind `hidden lg:block` without providing a mobile alternative.
- Don't make the sidebar navigation invisible on mobile without a topbar replacement.
- Don't use `overflow-hidden` on the `<body>` or root layout — it breaks iOS momentum scrolling.
- Don't add `hover:` effects without checking they degrade gracefully on touch (no hover state).
- Don't use fixed `height` on containers that hold dynamic text content.

## 11. Testing checklist (before shipping any UI change)

- [ ] Works at 375 px width (Chrome DevTools, iPhone SE profile)
- [ ] Works at 768 px width (iPad portrait)
- [ ] No horizontal scroll at any breakpoint (unless intentional + inside a scrollable container)
- [ ] All tap targets ≥ 44 × 44 px
- [ ] Text is readable without zooming at 375 px
- [ ] Table does not overflow viewport
- [ ] Dropdown panels do not overflow viewport
- [ ] Filter bar is usable on mobile (scrollable strip or dropdown)
